CHEESY BABY MARROW BREAD Makes 1 loafIngredients:350g baby marrows5ml (1 tsp) salt180g (1 cup) flour10ml (2 tsp) baking powder5ml (1 tsp) paprika2.5ml (1/2 tsp) garlic saltPinch of plain salt3 large eggs80ml (1/3 cup) milk80ml (1/3 cup) olive oil5ml (1 tsp) dried mixed herbs100g grated cheddar7 easy-to-bake breadsMethod:1) Coarsely grate the baby marrows. Place in a colander and sprinkle with 5ml (1tsp) salt. Set aside for 30 minutes for the moisture to drain.2) Preheat the oven to 180 C. Line a medium loaf pan with bake paper and grease with butter.3) Sift the flour, baking powder, paprika, garlic salt and a pinch of plain salt into a mixing bowl.4) In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs with the milk and olive oil until combined.5) Add the egg mixture to the dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in the dried mixed herbs and grated cheddar cheese.6) Squeeze excess moisture out of the baby marrows and mix gently into the batter.7) Spoon into the prepared loaf pan, smoothing the top. Sprinkle with an extra handful of grated cheese and bake for 45-55 minutes or until a skewer inserted into the bread comes out clean. Serve warm with butter. GLUTEN-FREE SODA BREAD WITH ROSEMARY &amp; RAISINS Makes 1 loafIngredients:250g (2 cups) almond flourA pinch of salt7.5ml (1 tsp) bicarbonate of soda30ml (2 tbsp) raisins15ml (1 tbsp) chopped fresh rosemary2 extra-large eggs15ml (1 tbsp) runny honey30ml (2 tbsp) cider vinegarMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) In a large bowl, combine the almond flour, salt, bicarbonate of soda, raisins and rosemary.3) In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs with the honey and vinegar.4) Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, mix to combine and shape into a round loaf. Place on a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper and cut a cross on top, using a serrated knife.5) Bake for 20 -30 minutes, then turn off the oven and leave the bread in for another 10 minutes. Serve warm with lots of butter. MEDITERRANEAN FOCACCIA Makes 1 foccaciaIngredients:Store-bought olive focaccia loaf125g softened butter1 finely chopped garlic clove5ml (1 tsp) Italian dried herbsThick slices of mozzarella cheese30ml (2 tbsp) chopped capers or pitted sliced olivesA few sun-dried tomatoes in oil, drained and cut into slivers 3 unique soup recipes that ll bowl you over this winterMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) Slice the focaccia into slices without cutting right through to the bottom.3) Mix the butter with the garlic and herbs. Spread this onto each slice of bread.4) Push a thick slice of mozzarella cheese between each focaccia slice and sprinkle over the capers or olives and sun-dried tomatoes.5) Wrap the loaf in foil and bake for 10 minutes, then open the top of the foil and return to the oven for a further 10-15 minutes until the bread is crispy and the cheese melted. Serve warm.